    <name>
				<text>10.2.3.11 Find mod and Arg (NOT IN QUIZ)</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<p>Find the modulus and argument of \( z =\displaystyle \dfrac{({@z1@})^{@n1@} \cdot ({@z2@})^{@n2@}}{({@z3@})^{@n3@}} \)</p>

<li><p> \( |z| = \) [[input:ans1]] (Give an exact answer) [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]&nbsp;</p></li>

<li><p> \( \text{arg}(z) = \)&nbsp;[[input:ans2]] (Give your answer to 3 d.p.)&nbsp;[[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]</p></li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
    <p>\( z_1 = {@z1@} \) so \( |z_1| = {@r1@} \) and&nbsp;&nbsp;\( \text{arg}(z_1) = {@theta1@}\)&nbsp;</p>
    <p>\( z_2 = {@z2@} \) so \( |z_2| = {@r2@} \) and&nbsp;&nbsp;\( \text{arg}(z_2) = {@theta2@}\)&nbsp;<br></p>
    <p></p>
    <p>\( z_3 = {@z3@} \) so \( |z_3| = {@r3@} \) and&nbsp;&nbsp;\( \text{arg}(z_3) = {@theta3@}\)&nbsp;</p>
    <p></p>
    <li>
        <p> \( |z| = \dfrac{|z_1|^{@n1@} |z_2|^{@n2@}}{|z_3|^{@n3@}} =&nbsp;&nbsp;\dfrac{({@r1@}^{@n1@}) \cdot ({@r2@}^{@n2@})}{{@r3@}^{@n3@}}&nbsp; = \displaystyle {@ta1@} \)<br></p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>\( \text{arg}(z) = {@n1@}\text{arg}(z_1)&nbsp;+ {@n2@}\text{arg}(z_2) -&nbsp;{@n3@}\text{arg}(z_3) = {@ta2@} \)</p>
    </li>
    <p>Have in mind that \( -\pi &lt; \text{arg}(z) \leq \pi \) so you may need to add or subtract a \( \pi\) from your \( \text{arg} \) results.</p>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
